This paper deals with data structures and their time complexity, which falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves conjectures related to computational complexity, which could place it in the categories of cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The use of fully retroactive queries for lower bounds could also relate to computational geometry (cs.CG) or graph theory (cs.GT).
